Sample Spine Surgeons Across Insurance Scenarios (Detailed Logging)

Source: R/phase2_sample_surgeons.R
phase2_sample_surgeons.Rd

This function expands a dataset of physicians by assigning multiple insurance types to each physician while retaining all original columns. It logs inputs, outputs, data transformations, and file paths to the console using the logger package.

Usage

phase2_sample_surgeons(
  data,
  insurance_types = c("Medicare", "Medicaid", "BCBS"),
  ensure_unique_phone_numbers = TRUE,
  output_csv_path = NULL,
  seed = 1978,
  specialty_column = "specialty_primary",
  npi_column = "NPI"
)

Arguments

data

A dataframe containing physician information. Must include columns for specialty, NPI, and phone number.

insurance_types

A character vector of insurance types to assign to each physician. Default is c("Medicare", "Medicaid", "BCBS").

ensure_unique_phone_numbers

Logical indicating whether to ensure unique phone numbers among physicians before expansion. Default is TRUE.

output_csv_path

Directory to save the output CSV file. If NULL, no file is saved. Default is NULL.

seed

An integer to set the random seed for reproducibility. Default is 1978.

specialty_column

The name of the column representing the specialty. Default is "specialty_primary".

npi_column

The name of the column representing the NPI. Default is "NPI".

Value

A dataframe with expanded rows, including one for each physician-insurance combination.

Examples

# Example 1: Basic usage with default parameters
physicians <- data.frame(
  specialty_primary = c("Orthopedics", "Cardiology"),
  NPI = c("1234567890", "9876543210"),
  phone_number = c("123-456-7890", "098-765-4321")
)
expanded_data <- phase2_sample_surgeons(
  data = physicians
)

# Example 3: Ensuring unique phone numbers and using a custom seed

  specialty_primary = c("Orthopedics", "Cardiology", "Orthopedics"),
  NPI = c("1234567890", "9876543210", "1234567890"),
  phone_number = c("123-456-7890", "098-765-4321", "123-456-7890")
)
expanded_data <- phase2_sample_surgeons(
  data = physicians,
  ensure_unique_phone_numbers = TRUE,
  seed = 42
)
